ools, Democracy, Deliberation, and Education illustrates how ordinary folks build and sustain their vision for a community and its future through consequential public decision making.For all the research on school boards conducted in recent years, no other project so directly addresses school boards as deliberative policymaking bodies. Democracy, Deliberation, and Education draws from 250 school-board meetings and 31 interviews with board members and administrators to offer insight into participants' varied understandings of their roles in the complex mechanism of governance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDeliberative democracyzWisconsin. 0aDemocracy and educationzWisconsin. 0aEducation and statezWisconsin. 0aSchool boardszWisconsin. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311074525240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271073163zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271073163423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271073163.jpg  a978-3-11-074525-2  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK